Installation from source
MPC is built using CMAKE - for more information see www.cmake.org

1) $cd build/
2) $cmake .. or $ccmake ..
3) make

Dependencies:
GNU Scientific Library - for interpolation

Optional dependencies:
Python and SWIG - to use MPC from python
OpenMP - for shared memory parallelization
FFTW - for turbulent magnetic field
Gadget - for smooth particle large scale structure
GTest - for unit-tests

To use MPC from python the following environment variables have to be set.
PYTHONPATH=[path to mpc.py]
MPC_DATA_PATH=[path to mpc/data]

Notes for Intel Compiler:
  -DCMAKE_SHARED_LINKER_FLAGS="-lifcore" -DCMAKE_Fortran_COMPILER=ifort
